Q)write a Java stream program to Find the First Non-Repeating Character in the below String?

ðŸ”†Ans)let's break it down

âœ…ï¸step 1) convert the strings to chars array

âœ…ï¸step 2) call mapToObj () to convert to char obj .

âœ…ï¸step 3) call Collectors.groupingBy () to get chars and its count in a Map.

âœ…ï¸step 4) call entrySet () and stream() tobget the map into stream.

âœ…ï¸step 5) call filter() with getValue ()==1 to get the 1st occurrence.

âœ…ï¸step 6)call map to get the char which is having 1 occurrence and call findFirst() to get the first occurrence char

âŒï¸â“ï¸String input = "Java articles are awesome";

ðŸŒ³ðŸ‘‰Expected Output: 'J'

ðŸ—³Example:
ðŸ‘‡

 Character result = input.chars()
 .mapToObj(c -> (char) c)
 .collect(Collectors
 .groupingBy(Function.identity(), LinkedHashMap::new, Collectors
 .counting()))

 .entrySet()
 .stream()
 .filter(e -> e.getValue() == 1)
 .map(Map.Entry::getKey)
 .findFirst()
 .orElse(null);